This paper is about evaluating Sentence Boundary Detection (SBD) systems, which is a subfield of Natural Language Processing (NLP). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a new metric for evaluation, which involves multi-reference (dis)agreement, which could fall under the categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper uses standard evaluation metrics, which could fall under cs.SD (Software Engineering) or cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
